00:18:00.939 --> 00:18:02.660
There's lots of data to play with.

00:18:02.660 --> 00:18:08.219
I encourage anybody who's interested in the data to go do that.

00:18:08.219 --> 00:18:23.260
Oh, right here.

00:18:23.260 --> 00:18:30.859
And my main question is, are you considering, do you consider public health as research

00:18:30.859 --> 00:18:34.660
regarding the tools that RCU provide?

00:18:34.660 --> 00:18:39.859
And my second question is, when you're reaching out for teaching, are you looking for the

00:18:39.859 --> 00:18:42.180
specific area like public health?

00:18:42.180 --> 00:18:47.619
We're a little bit stuck with SAS because it was kind of funded by the federal government

00:18:47.619 --> 00:18:52.219
and people don't have anything else to use but what is available to them.

00:18:52.219 --> 00:18:53.219
Thank you.

00:18:53.219 --> 00:18:56.260
So, I'm not sure I heard the first part of the question very well.

00:18:56.260 --> 00:18:57.260
Could you say it again?

00:18:57.260 --> 00:19:04.500
And that's the most important question is, you said RCU is providing the tool, half price

00:19:04.500 --> 00:19:08.260
I think, for research and free for education.

00:19:08.260 --> 00:19:14.020
Where public health fall, is it research or whatever you call it, to benefit from those

00:19:14.020 --> 00:19:16.819
discount?

00:19:16.819 --> 00:19:18.459
What results have we seen from this?

00:19:18.459 --> 00:19:22.900
I think maybe if I could rephrase the question, are you trying to figure out if public health

00:19:22.900 --> 00:19:29.180
as an area of study is considered research or teaching and if you get the 50% off versus

00:19:29.180 --> 00:19:30.180
the full free?

00:19:30.180 --> 00:19:31.180
Is that the question?

00:19:31.180 --> 00:19:32.180
Yeah, exactly.

00:19:32.180 --> 00:19:33.180
That's the question.

00:19:33.180 --> 00:19:34.180
Okay.

00:19:34.180 --> 00:19:38.219
The easy decision is, do you have a syllabus of teaching for students?

00:19:38.219 --> 00:19:41.099
If you have a syllabus, then you're a teacher.

00:19:41.099 --> 00:19:44.819
If you don't have a syllabus, if you're doing research, then you're a researcher.

00:19:44.819 --> 00:19:45.819
It's really that simple.

